			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">52.237-9</ph> Waiver of Limitation on Severance Payments to Foreign Nationals.</title>
		    <conbody outputclass="clause" class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <p id="d3562e13" class="- topic/p ">As prescribed in <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1077959.dita#i1077959"
                     base="i1077959"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">37.113-2</xref>(b)</ph>, use the following clause:</p>
			      <p outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps" class="- topic/p ">Waiver of Limitation on Severance Payments to Foreign Nationals (May 2014)</p>
			      <ol id="d3544e25" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d3562e29" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Pursuant to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2324(e)(3)(A)</xref> or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 4304(b)(1)</xref>, as applicable, the cost allowability limitations in FAR <xref href="FAR-i1084735.dita#i1084735"
                        base="i1084735"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">31.205-6</xref>(g)(6) are waived.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d3562e47" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
